<div id="review_4125440631" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4125440631" />
    <a title="Humberto González" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15636980-humberto-gonz-lez"><img alt="Humberto González" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355982539p2/15636980.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4125440631?book_show_action=true">Jul 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Humberto González" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Humberto González" href="/user/show/15636980-humberto-gonz-lez">Humberto González</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780156075107" href="/book/show/665267.Andromache">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4125440631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11589406215289409264">Another Racine to complement my ISOLT journey. This play offers compelling observations on passion, duty, and the love that&apos;s incomplete without inflamed hate. I enjoyed the mirroring between characters, the metonymic &quot;eye&quot; that pervades the work, and the amused (and bemused) cackle that I let out with Hermione&apos;s appalled surprise when she learns that Orestes has killed Pyrrhus at her request.</span>
  <span id="freeText11589406215289409264" style="display:none">Another Racine to complement my ISOLT journey. This play offers compelling observations on passion, duty, and the love that's incomplete without inflamed hate. I enjoyed the mirroring between characters, the metonymic "eye" that pervades the work, and the amused (and bemused) cackle that I let out with Hermione's appalled surprise when she learns that Orestes has killed Pyrrhus at her request.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11589406215289409264" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


